The Fight in the Fields: Csar Chvez and the Farm Workers' Struggle
Documentary
This film explores the pivotal role played by the United Farm Workers and its leader Csar Chvez in organizing the first successful union for farm workers.
While focusing on Chvez, the film portrays the Chicano activism of the 1960s and 1970s and the training of a generation of organizers in their struggle for social and economic justice.
